<br>
Personally I form groups in a way that each group could work as its own little &quot;commando&quot; on the raid, so the group would still be able to hold its own in tricky situations or when it gets seperated from the rest or something. Normally the groups I form in raids look something like:<br>
<br>
Melee (Paladin/Shadowknight/Warrior)<br>
Porter (Druid/Wizard)<br>
Slower (Shaman/Enchanter)<br>
Healer (Cleric/Druid)<br>
Support (Mage/Ranger/Beastlord/Necromancer/Rogue/Bard)<br>
Random<br>
<br>
I try to use this setup for every group in the raid, of course it's not always working due to lack of the appropriate classes available. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqsigs.screamparks.net/images/hosted/Karlea.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
