It can still be viable of course but you'll find that experienced raid leaders will pretty much toss this system out the window.<br>
Need to keep healers pumped with mana? Group as many as you can with a bard and necro. Need a mob dead right now without question or you'll die to it's unresistable AE? Put those five trueshot rangers with a bard for overhaste.<br>
There's many different possibilities depending on what the raid target is. The raid should be designed around what you're going after instead of trying to find ways to make your raid work with a standard setup. Doing this requires practice and alot of experience. Mostly though, just use the standard group setup and it should work well enough to get by.<br>
<br>
Dory <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trump13>Trump13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/24/03 12:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4647.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How are you making groups in raids?</span><hr size=1> I agree... in most cases you need to design your raid based on the circumstances.<br>
<br>
General rule is to keep at least one healer (cleric, druid, shaman) in each group.   Most raids involve just one MA and one cleric to keep track of the MA, so keeping the bard with the MA group is a good idea.  Many times I'll throw a paladin or 2 in the MA group just in case, because Lay Hands can be a life saver.  Having the necro in the group with the main cleric for ticks to keep the raid moving faster helps too.<br>
<br>
There are different circumstances though.  Like going against a dragon with a resistable AE spell, you may want to group all the casters together with a cleric and bard to keep them alive.<br>
<br>
That's half the fun, deciding the best way to tackle a situaion.<br>
<br>
